abs(decimal).name: abs
abs(decimal).description: Returns the absolute value of the specified Decimal.

abs(double).name: abs
abs(double).description: Returns the absolute value of the specified Double.

abs(integer).name: abs
abs(integer).description: Returns the absolute value of the specified Integer.

abs(long).name: abs
abs(long).description: Returns the absolute value of the specified Long.

acos(decimal).name: acos
acos(decimal).description: Returns the arc cosine of an angle, in the range of 0.0 through pi.

acos(double).name: acos
acos(double).description: Returns the arc cosine of an angle, in the range of 0.0 through pi.

asin(decimal).name: asin
asin(decimal).description: Returns the arc sine of an angle, in the range of -pi/2 through pi/2.

asin(double).name: asin
asin(double).description: Returns the arc sine of an angle, in the range of -pi/2 through pi/2.

atan(decimal).name: atan
atan(decimal).description: Returns the arc tangent of an angle, in the range of -pi/2 through pi/2.

atan(double).name: atan
atan(double).description: Returns the arc tangent of an angle, in the range of -pi/2 through pi/2.

atan2(decimal,decimal).name: atan2
atan2(decimal,decimal).signature: public static Decimal atan2(Decimal xCoordinate, Decimal yCoordinate)
atan2(decimal,decimal).description: Converts rectangular coordinates (xCoordinate and yCoordinate) to polar (r and theta). This method computes the phase theta by computing an arc tangent of xCoordinate/yCoordinate in the range of -pi to pi.

atan2(double,double).name: atan2
atan2(double,double).signature: public static Double atan2(Double xCoordinate, Double yCoordinate)
atan2(double,double).description: Converts rectangular coordinates (xCoordinate and yCoordinate) to polar (r and theta). This method computes the phase theta by computing an arc tangent of xCoordinate/yCoordinate in the range of -pi to pi.

cbrt(decimal).name: cbrt
cbrt(decimal).description: Returns the cube root of the specified Decimal. The cube root of a negative value is the negative of the cube root of that value's magnitude.

cbrt(double).name: cbrt
cbrt(double).description: Returns the cube root of the specified Double. The cube root of a negative value is the negative of the cube root of that value's magnitude.

ceil(decimal).name: ceil
ceil(decimal).description: Returns the smallest (closest to negative infinity) Decimal that is not less than the argument and is equal to a mathematical integer.

ceil(double).name: ceil
ceil(double).description: Returns the smallest (closest to negative infinity) Double that is not less than the argument and is equal to a mathematical integer.

cos(decimal).name: cos
cos(decimal).description: Returns the trigonometric cosine of the angle specified by decimalAngle.

cos(double).name: cos
cos(double).description: Returns the trigonometric cosine of the angle specified by doubleAngle.

cosh(decimal).name: cosh
cosh(decimal).description: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of decimalAngle. The hyperbolic cosine of d is defined to be (ex + e-x)/2 where e is Euler's number.

cosh(double).name: cosh
cosh(double).description: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of doubleAngle. The hyperbolic cosine of d is defined to be (ex + e-x)/2 where e is Euler's number.

exp(decimal).name: exp
exp(decimal).description: Returns Euler's number e raised to the power of the specified Decimal.

exp(double).name: exp
exp(double).description: Returns Euler's number e raised to the power of the specified Double.

floor(decimal).name: floor
floor(decimal).description: Returns the largest (closest to positive infinity) Decimal that is not greater than the argument and is equal to a mathematical integer.

floor(double).name: floor
floor(double).description: Returns the largest (closest to positive infinity) Double that is not greater than the argument and is equal to a mathematical integer.

log(decimal).name: log
log(decimal).description: Returns the natural logarithm (base e) of the specified Decimal.

log(double).name: log
log(double).description: Returns the natural logarithm (base e) of the specified Double.

log10(decimal).name: log10
log10(decimal).description: Returns the logarithm (base 10) of the specified Decimal.

log10(double).name: log10
log10(double).description: Returns the logarithm (base 10) of the specified Double.

max(decimal,decimal).name: max
max(decimal,decimal).signature: public static Decimal max(Decimal decimalValue1, Decimal decimalValue2)
max(decimal,decimal).description: Returns the larger of the two specified Decimals.

max(double,double).name: max
max(double,double).signature: public static Double max(Double doubleValue1, Double doubleValue2)
max(double,double).description: Returns the larger of the two specified Doubles.

max(integer,integer).name: max
max(integer,integer).signature: public static Integer max(Integer integerValue1, Integer integerValue2)
max(integer,integer).description: Returns the larger of the two specified Integers.

max(long,long).name: max
max(long,long).signature: public static Long max(Long longValue1, Long longValue2)
max(long,long).description: Returns the larger of the two specified Longs.

min(decimal,decimal).name: min
min(decimal,decimal).signature: public static Decimal min(Decimal decimalValue1, Decimal decimalValue2)
min(decimal,decimal).description: Returns the smaller of the two specified Decimals.

min(double,double).name: min
min(double,double).signature: public static Double min(Double doubleValue1, Double doubleValue2)
min(double,double).description: Returns the smaller of the two specified Doubles.

min(integer,integer).name: min
min(integer,integer).signature: public static Integer min(Integer integerValue1, Integer integerValue2)
min(integer,integer).description: Returns the smaller of the two specified Integers.

min(long,long).name: min
min(long,long).signature: public static Long min(Long longValue1, Long longValue2)
min(long,long).description: Returns the smaller of the two specified Longs.

mod(integer,integer).name: mod
mod(integer,integer).signature: public static Integer mod(Integer integerValue1, Integer integerValue2)
mod(integer,integer).description: Returns the remainder of integerValue1 divided by integerValue2.

mod(long,long).name: mod
mod(long,long).signature: public static Long mod(Long longValue1, Long longValue2)
mod(long,long).description: Returns the remainder of longValue1 divided by longValue2.

pow(double,double).name: pow
pow(double,double).signature: public static Double pow(Double doubleValue, Double exponent)
pow(double,double).description: Returns the value of the first Double raised to the power of exponent.

random().name: random
random().description: Returns a positive Double that is greater than or equal to 0.0 and less than 1.0.

rint(decimal).name: rint
rint(decimal).description: Returns the value that is closest in value to decimalValue and is equal to a mathematical integer.

rint(double).name: rint
rint(double).description: Returns the value that is closest in value to doubleValue and is equal to a mathematical integer.

round(double).name: round
round(double).description: Do not use. This method is deprecated as of the Winter '08 release. Instead, use Math.roundToLong. Returns the closest Integer to the specified Double. If the result is less than -2,147,483,648 or greater than 2,147,483,647, Apex generates an error.

round(decimal).name: round
round(decimal).description: Returns the rounded approximation of this Decimal. The number  is rounded to zero decimal places using half-even rounding mode, that is, it rounds towards the nearest neighbor unless both neighbors are equidistant, in which case, this mode rounds towards the even neighbor.

roundtolong(decimal).name: roundToLong
roundtolong(decimal).description: Returns the rounded approximation of this Decimal. The number  is rounded to zero decimal places using half-even rounding mode, that is, it rounds towards the nearest neighbor unless both neighbors are equidistant, in which case, this mode rounds towards the even neighbor.

roundtolong(double).name: roundToLong
roundtolong(double).description: Returns the closest Long to the specified Double.

signum(decimal).name: signum
signum(decimal).description: Returns the signum function of the specified Decimal, which is 0 if decimalValue is 0, 1.0 if decimalValue is greater than 0, -1.0 if decimalValue is less than 0.

signum(double).name: signum
signum(double).description: Returns the signum function of the specified Double, which is 0 if doubleValue is 0, 1.0 if doubleValue is greater than 0, -1.0 if doubleValue is less than 0.

sin(decimal).name: sin
sin(decimal).description: Returns the trigonometric sine of the angle specified by decimalAngle.

sin(double).name: sin
sin(double).description: Returns the trigonometric sine of the angle specified by doubleAngle.

sinh(decimal).name: sinh
sinh(decimal).description: Returns the hyperbolic sine of decimalAngle. The hyperbolic sine of decimalAngle is defined to be (ex - e-x)/2 where e is Euler's number.

sinh(double).name: sinh
sinh(double).description: Returns the hyperbolic sine of doubleAngle. The hyperbolic sine of doubleAngle is defined to be (ex - e-x)/2 where e is Euler's number.

sqrt(decimal).name: sqrt
sqrt(decimal).description: Returns the correctly rounded positive square root of decimalValue.

sqrt(double).name: sqrt
sqrt(double).description: Returns the correctly rounded positive square root of doubleValue.

tan(decimal).name: tan
tan(decimal).description: Returns the trigonometric tangent of the angle specified by decimalAngle.

tan(double).name: tan
tan(double).description: Returns the trigonometric tangent of the angle specified by doubleAngle.

tanh(decimal).name: tanh
tanh(decimal).description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of decimalAngle. The hyperbolic tangent of decimalAngle is defined to be (ex - e-x)/(ex + e-x) where e is Euler's number. In other words, it is equivalent to sinh(x)/cosinh(x). The absolute value of the exact tanh is always less than 1.

tanh(double).name: tanh
tanh(double).description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of doubleAngle. The hyperbolic tangent of doubleAngle is defined to be (ex - e-x)/(ex + e-x) where e is Euler's number. In other words, it is equivalent to sinh(x)/cosinh(x). The absolute value of the exact tanh is always less than 1.
